notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Kernel-based Virtual Machine (KVM) offers a full virtualization solution forLinux on numerous hardware platforms. The virt:rhel module contains packageswhich provide user-space components used to run virtual machines using KVM.The packages also provide APIs for managing and interacting with the virtualized systems.

Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):

* virtiofsd --help and manpage does not agree on --thread-pool-size default value (JIRA:Rocky Linux-26197)

* Frequent VM pauses on OpenShift Virtualization with Portworx storage (JIRA:Rocky Linux-60553)

This advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.
